oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Leonard Melton Sr. pictured with the fish caught on Kentucky Lake, Tenn.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of Leonard Melton, Sr. and the three fish he took on Kentucky Lake. He is pictured at the rocky shoreline in a fishing boat with miscellaneous fishing gear and supplies. The lake and treeline is pictured in the background. Melton is wearing a hat, shirt and pants.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
